dc_description_s: This data represents zoning for Portage County, Wisconsin in 2021 and includes the layers 'Portage_Airport_2021,' 'Portage_General_2021,' and 'Portage_Shoreland_2021.'[Airport: Polygon grid with values above mean sea level (MSL NAVD 1927) that are the maximum elevation of structures within the zone.General:Polygon features depicting boundaries of zoning districts. Used to implement the Portage County zoning ordinance. Polygons are typically extended to center of right of way unless specifically required to be different. Otherwise tax parcel boundaries are followed where possible. Shoreland: Polygon data depicting shoreland zone for lakes and impoundments. Water bodies are included if they have a history of holding water in 2000, 2005, 2010 Portage County Aerial photography.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data available, please visit: https://www.co.portage.wi.us/department/planning-zoning/land-information-gis/maps-and-gis-data
